CONVERSATION TITLE: Cisco Intersight - Cloud operations platform for hybrid IT
CONTENT:
Dear Ajay,


Whether you use the cloud-based portal or a local appliance, Cisco Intersight combines the benefits of cloud-based management with security similar to that of on-premises systems. This management and automation platform is enhanced by analytics and machine learning techniques to increase efficiency so you can manage the growing complexity of your IT infrastructure.


You can extend the current investment in Intersight to:

 

1. Simplify your operations 

Extend your Intersight investment from management of computing infrastructure to work across your full stack to provide management & operations of hypervisors on-prem (VMware, KVM), on cloud (AWS, Azure) in “cloud like way” using Intersight Virtualization service


2. Accelerate Application Modernization Journey 

Simplify your K8s strategy across hybrid cloud environment, enabling easy deployment, management and lifecycle of K8s clusters through secure enterprise curated, 100% upstream based Intersight K8s service 


3. Continuously optimize 

Enhance your environment using intelligence provided by Intersight workload optimizer to manage application resources across any environment with real time, full stack visibility to provide automated recommendations to ensure performance and better cost control warranting applications always run-in desired state & at optimal costs


4. Intersight Service for Terraform 

It acts as a bridge for DevOps enabling Infrastructure- as-code automation for private and public cloud environments delivered as Secure SaaS linking Intersight to Hashicorp Terraform Cloud for business allowing you to embrace IaC automation

 

To learn more about Cisco Intersight, click here to sign up for a customized workshop, or to speak to one of our experts.

CONVERSATION TITLE: Explore Columbia’s M.S. in Construction Administration
CONTENT:
Hi Ajay,


As the Academic Director of the Master of Science in Construction Administration at Columbia University's School of Professional Studies, I'd like to take a moment to introduce myself and the program.


I joined the SPS Construction Administration master's program in 2015 following a 17+ year career in urban development, construction, as well as M&A in the real estate sector; and I have worked alongside nonprofits and public agencies on urban space use and revitalization.


Columbia’s Master of Science in Construction Administration program prepares graduates for a variety of careers at the forefront of construction and project leadership. Graduates develop rewarding careers with some of the world's most respected architecture, engineering, and construction firms, entrusted with delivering some of the most impactful projects of our time.


Available part-time and full-time, the master's degree in Construction Administration at Columbia University provides an exceptional understanding of the complexities of the industry from current leaders in the field (AECOM, Gilbane, Turner, Related, MTA, and more) with world-class expertise. Furthermore, the program's close relationship with CMAA, AIA, ULI, the Royal Institute of Chartered Surveyors (RICS), and Professional Women in Construction (PWC), provides unparalleled networking, access, and thought leadership at a local, national, and global level.


I hope you will consider applying to Columbia. Click here for more information about the M.S. in Construction Administration. If you would like to set up a time to discuss the program, you can email my team at construction@sps.columbia.edu.


Best,


Francisco Pineda | Academic Director

Columbia University, School of Professional Studies

CONVERSATION TITLE: Are you prepared for the post-corona economy in AI?
CONTENT:
Hello Ajay,


Every day I see new headlines about the effect that COVID-19 has had on the industry. It’s put us all in a state of uncertainty about the job market and industry prospects. But this isn’t the first time I’ve faced this kind of situation. 


Back in 2008, it was a similar situation when the recession happened. Nobody knew what the future was going to be like, but if you look back, you’ll know that the industry bounced back. That’s because we focused on technologies of the future to make better decisions. And the technology of our current future is Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning. 


It is to help professionals learn the right skill in this domain and future-proof their careers, we’d launched the PG Program in AI and Machine Learning, in collaboration with The University of Texas at Austin.


It’s been ranked as India’s #1 Program due to exceptional faculty, dedicated learning support, industry-relevant curriculum and career assistance. The program is designed for working professionals to gain the skills they’ll need to build rewarding careers. 


If you’ve been looking to start your AI career and have not been sure where to start, this program might be what you’re looking for. You can see for yourself and learn more by downloading the brochure from the link below.


Happy Learning!

CONVERSATION TITLE: Become a Data Scientist
CONTENT:
Hi Ajay,


While reading many of the Tech in 2020 lists over the past month, I was pleasantly surprised to note that Data Science had found such widespread adoption. We’ve always known that data science would be the future, but the way it quickly scaled to make organizations more data-driven has been astounding. Another crucial trend was how companies are still struggling to find qualified talent. This situation of high demand and low supply of qualified professionals has paved the way for aspiring professionals to build a rewarding career if they upskill themselves.


To help professionals like yourself gain the right skills and chart a rewarding career path with the right credentials, Great Lakes Executive Learning, and Great Learning have collaborated to offer the PG Program in Data Science and Engineering. 


The 9-month program is delivered in a live-online learning format so that you can upskill without having to quit your job. It features a comprehensive curriculum that includes a series of theory lectures and hands-on projects that will enable you to gain industry-relevant and practical skill sets. Learning is delivered by leading data science academicians, and the program journey also includes a capstone project to further bolster your industry expertise. On completion, you’ll receive a PG Certificate from Great Lakes Executive Learning, which you can showcase as a testament of your expertise. 


If you’ve been wanting to upskill yourself in Data Science but have not been sure how, this program would help you get well on your way to launching your Data Science career. If you’d like to know more, just click below;


Happy Learning!
